AR-001 through AR-011 are implemented under the most consistent on-disk mapping: the first eleven requirement blocks in `specs/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md`. The repo initially contained only `specs/`, so I built the minimal Go skeleton from those specs and the matching design notes rather than extending preexisting source.

The main implementation is in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`, `pkg/common/types/types.go`, and `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`. That covers the `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` API types, scheme registration, JSON contracts, shared request/response structs, request validation, `GET /health`, the `/v1` route surface, handler-side kind overriding, and success response wiring. I also added CRD manifests in `manifests/charts/base/crds/` so the status subresources, `Age` printer column, defaults, enums, and namespaced scope are represented explicitly on disk.

Verification is partial but concrete. I added spec-driven tests in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go`, `pkg/common/types/types_test.go`, and `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` to cover the CRD metadata, serialization shape, validation rules, middleware ordering, route registration, and response shape. I was not able to execute `go test ./...` here because shell execution is blocked in this environment, so runtime verification is still pending. A final local pass should be `go mod tidy` followed by `go test ./...` once command execution is available.
